<br>
Root, Stun.  Mage pets can do this.  Shadow step, snare, I'll give you that.<br>
But the plain fact of the matter is, they have a tank.  I don't see how this can be any clearer.  Tanks allow the caster to do his job without contest.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;you state that they are about on par with us for damage.&quot;<br>
<br>
When mage spells are about 10%-20% less effective than ours, plus a pet, I feel that equals even or greater damage.  I hunt with my good mage buddy all the time.  He seems to do more damage than myself, both using the same mana.  I say &quot;seems&quot; because I don't take notes on how much damage his pet does. =)<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Please give examples. I can't think of *any* recent additions.. or even not-so-recent additions.&quot;<br>
Equipment Equipment Equipment. =)<br>
Feh, forget the whole additions point.  Regardless of whether I&quot;m a moron or not (no votes please! =P ), regardless of whether or not classes are getting better or always have been better, I feel that wizzies are harder to play and get less out of it than many classes.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'll just cite what I know.  My mage friends seem to always do equal or greater damage in groups.  My druid friends can solo like none other (besides necros), buff and harmony and dot and DD in groups just fine, TP, etc.  My warrior friends seem to have a much easier life leveling and grouping than I.  And please don't bring up &quot;They can't cast&quot; stuff.  Generally, all good warriors have plenty of caster friends. =)  Buffs and traveling aren't a problem.  I find that wizzies are generally harder to play for myself, and I see that we're getting less out of it later on.<br>
<br>
/sigh<br>
<br>
I feel that I'm a competant player, and my competant friends seem to have it easier.  Plain and simple.  I don't know how else to put it.  Part of my arguement is just backing up what I hear a good number of higher level wizzies talking about.<br>
<br>
I just don't know how to explain it. =(  Anyone help shed some light on my screwed up head? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ueliathen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliathen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/5/01 11:15:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What The Sleeper taught me about wizards</span><hr size=1> cduckman:<br>
<br>
The only thing I can really suggest is that you either take my word (and the word of anyone else who knows), or make a second character.  One of the characters that you say &quot;seem&quot; to have it a little bit better.<br>
<br>
It is easy to look at someone's spell line up and often it looks sweet.  But, when trying one of those classes, you will quickly learn that they have the same types of complaints.  Each and every class has a lot of issues.  That is part of the &quot;vision&quot; as set forth by Verant.  They want each class to have weaknesses, so that we group up with people.<br>
<br>
I won't begin to go on about bolt spells for mages.  The lack of different types of offensive spells for druids and mages (fire).  I'm not going to make a huge list of downsides to all the classes, but trust me. They all have them.<br>
<br>
You also may want to consider turning on your /log and parsing some data when grouped with your magician friends.<br>
<br>
More importantly, if you are starting to wish you had one of those other classes, seriously think about switching.  The wizard class isn't for everybody.  Just some things to consider.  The reason you can't think of any enhancements to other classes besides &quot;twinking&quot; is because there haven't been.<br>
<br>
I'm not trying to come off rude here.  But a lot of the time people start to believe what they hear.. and that doesn't make it true.<br>
<br>
<br>
P.S.  Never tell a mage that the ability of their pets to root/stun balances them with our ability to root/stun.  The two versions of spells are VERY VERY different. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zestifan>Zestifan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/01 3:29:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What The Sleeper taught me about wizards</span><hr size=1> &quot;They want each class to have weaknesses, so that we group up with people.&quot;<br>
<br>
Well wizards certainly have weaknesses and we do WANT TO GROUP.  The problem is we have so many holes in our class big enough to drive a truck through that groups don't particularly want wizards. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=422.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=399.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=371.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.threadControl?topicID=371.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=371.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=371.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswiza